  "prompt": "What is the best site to download songs?",
  "response": "There are several reputable sites where you can legally download songs, depending on your preferences, including whether you're looking for free or paid options. Here are some popular choices:\n\n1. **iTunes/Apple Music** - A well-known platform for purchasing and downloading music.\n\n2. **Amazon Music** - Offers a large selection of songs available for purchase and download.\n\n3. **Google Play Music** - Previously allowed users to buy and download music, but it's now integrated into YouTube Music.\n\n4. **Bandcamp** - Great for discovering independent artists and often allows for direct purchases.\n\n5. **Spotify** - While primarily a streaming service, Spotify Premium allows users to download songs for offline listening.\n\n6. **SoundCloud** - Some artists offer their tracks for free download; just look for the download button.\n\n7. **Jamendo** - A platform that focuses on independent artists, offering free downloads under Creative Commons licenses.\n\nAlways ensure that you are downloading music legally and supporting artists in a fair manner.",
